## 3. Data Model (L1 — Definition)

All custom objects are packaged. Names illustrative.

### `Form__c` (master definition)
- `Primary_Context_Object__c` (Text) — API name of the form-level primary SObject (e.g., `Account`).
- `Form_Type__c` (Picklist) — `Form` / `Survey`.
- `Status__c` (Picklist) — `Draft` / `Published`.
- `Schema_Snapshot__c` (Long Text / linked ContentVersion JSON) — frozen schema generated at publish. Contains, per referenced object: field metadata, picklist entries, dependency maps, record-type-scoped values. **This is what makes guest rendering possible.**
- `Layout_Config__c` (Long Text JSON) — page/section/grid structure, overrides, rules. (Can be normalized into child records instead — see note.)

### `Form_Section__c`
- `Form__c` (Master-Detail)
- `Sequence__c`, `Page_Number__c` (Number) — supports multi-page wizard.
- `Context_Type__c` (Picklist) — `Parent` / `Related_Child`.
- `Child_Relationship_Name__c` (Text) — populated when `Context_Type__c = Related_Child`; the relationship used to build the repeater.
- `Is_Repeater__c` (Checkbox) — auto-set true for child-context sections.
- `Max_Rows__c` / `Min_Rows__c` (Number) — repeater row limits.
- `Grid_Columns__c` (Number, 1–4) — dynamic grid layout.

### `Form_Element__c`
- `Form_Section__c` (Master-Detail)
- `Field_API_Name__c` (Text) — bound SObject field (implicit mapping target).
- `Sequence__c`, `Grid_Position__c`
- `Render_As__c` (Picklist) — `Default` / `Radio_Buttons` / `Custom_MultiSelect` / `Dropdown` etc. (input override)
- `Visibility_Rule__c` (Long Text JSON) — client-side show/hide/require logic.
- `Calculation_Formula__c` (Long Text) — cross-field calculation expression.
- `Default_Value_Token__c` (Text) — autofill token (`$URL.*`, `$Record.*`, `$User.*`), surface-aware (see §7).
- `Is_Required__c`, `Help_Text__c`, `Placeholder__c`

> **Normalization note:** sections/elements can be modeled either as child records (queryable, report-friendly) or as a single JSON blob on `Form__c` (fewer rows, faster load, easier versioning). Recommendation: child records for builder editing, but **compile to a single JSON definition + schema snapshot at publish** so the player loads one record, not a tree of SOQL. This also dodges player-side query governor pressure.

