## 7. Autofill Tokens — Surface-Aware (`$User.*`, `$Record.*`, `$URL.*`)

Tokens resolve differently per surface; the engine treats them uniformly but the adapter populates `dataContext` correctly:

| Token | Internal Record Page | Flow Screen | Public/External |
|-------|----------------------|-------------|-----------------|
| `$URL.*` | ✅ query params | ✅ query params | ✅ query params |
| `$Record.*` | ✅ from `recordId` | ✅ if a record var is passed in | ⚠️ only if an Id is passed in URL **and** guest read is granted via sharing rule |
| `$User.*` | ✅ running user | ✅ running user | ❌ resolves to the *site guest user*, not the submitter — **disable/hide** to avoid confusion and data leakage |

The builder should visually flag tokens that won't resolve on the form's target surface.

